KW  - fixed points
KW  - concavity
AB  - The square root function has a unique positive fixed point. This function has the following properties: it is strictly increasing and strictly concave, with f(0)=0, and there are points a≥0 and b≥0 such that f(a)≥a and f(b)≤b. It is shown that any function from Rn to Rn satisfying these properties has a unique positive fixed point. Journal of Economic Literature Classification Number: C62.
